03/05/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prosecutors are launching a probe stemming from an unprecedented scandal involving senior government officials, investigators and two key state-run companies, the Sofia heating distributor Toplofikatsiya and the tobacco holding Bulgartabac.
Chief Prosecutor Boris Velchev said on Wednesday (May 2nd) that everyone directly involved would be questioned.
Allegations of corruption, blackmail, and abuse of office were made recently by the head of the National Investigation Service, Angel Alexandrov, against Minister of Economy and Energy Rumen Ovcharov and the head of Bulgartabac, Hristo Lachev.
(Sega, Dnevnik - 03/05/07;
Darik, Mediapool - 02/05/07)
